            "comment": "Law: Free Cities & Supernatural Rights",
            "key": [
                "free city",
                "rights",
                "California",
                "safe state",
                "supernatural rights"
            ],
            "keysecondary": [],
            "selectiveLogic": 0,
            "content": "Supernaturals are publicly known and widespread worldwide; humans know of them, but their rights are NOT guaranteed everywhere. California is a rights-guaranteed state. Solarton and Blackwood are \"free cities\" where supernaturals need not hide. Outside free cities, exposure risks legal persecution, hostile humans, or supernatural-hunting factions: which is why mimicry applies on travel. This is what keeps the wolf/vampire politics contained to Blackwood's districts.",
